# Project Context

## Overview

- Java Spring Boot 4 web application, RESTful API, Maven (never Gradle)
- Language: **Java 25** — records, sealed classes, pattern matching, text blocks, virtual threads where applicable
- Architecture: **DDD + Hexagonal** (Ports & Adapters) — applied loosely and pragmatically

## Technology Stack

- Spring Boot 4 / Spring Framework 7 / Spring Security 7 — latest major versions
- SpringDoc OpenAPI 3, Jakarta Bean Validation 4
- JUnit 5 + Mockito + AssertJ, Micrometer + Actuator, HAPI FHIR client 8.x

## Project Structure

```
com/github/miguelsombrero/example
├── api/                     # Driving adapters
│   ├── controller/          # REST controllers
│   ├── mapper/              # DTO <-> Domain mappers
│   └── dto/                 # API request/response DTOs (records)
├── config/                  # Shared Spring @Configuration
├── exception/               # Exception classes and @RestControllerAdvice
├── domain/                  # Pure domain — entities, value objects, aggregates
├── infrastructure/          # Driven adapters
│   ├── client/              # HTTP client adapter (port implementation)
│   ├── config/              # External service config
│   └── mapper/              # External service <-> Domain mappers
├── service/                 # Application layer — port interfaces + use cases
└── util/                    # Utilities
```

**Layer mapping (DDD/Hexagonal applied loosely):**

- `domain/` — Pure domain. **No framework dependencies.** Entities, value objects, aggregates.
- `service/` — Thin application layer. Contains port interfaces and use-case orchestrators (no separate `application/` package).
- `api/` — Driving adapters. REST controllers, DTOs, mappers.
- `infrastructure/` — Driven adapters.

**Dependency rule:** domain → service → api/infrastructure. Never the reverse.

## Base Package & Build

- **Base package:** `com.github.miguelsombrero.*`
- **Build command:** `mvn test`
- **Test sources:** `src/test/java/com/github/miguelsombrero/*/`

## Conventions

- Constructor injection only — Lombok `@RequiredArgsConstructor`, `private final` fields
- One class per file; package names lowercase singular nouns
- Business logic in domain; never in controllers or adapters
- Ports defined in `service/`; adapters in `api/` and `infrastructure/`
